comments.body:
I'm not sure that I understand what you are asking for.

Normally, if you want to send the same message to multiple people, you would just add multiple mailboxes to the To/Cc/Bcc headers.

```csharp
message.To.Add(new MailboxAddress("Joe", "joe@example.com"));
message.To.Add(new MailboxAddress("Cindy", "cindy@example.com"));

await client.SendAsync(message);
```

If you want to send to multiple people but you don't want anyone who receives the message to be able to see who the other recipients are/were, then you can use the Blind-Carbon-Copy (aka Bcc) header. A common technique for doing this is:

```csharp
message.To.Add(new GroupAddress("undisclosed-recipients"));
message.Bcc.Add(new MailboxAddress("Joe", "joe@example.com"));
message.Bcc.Add(new MailboxAddress("Cindy", "cindy@example.com"));

await client.SendAsync(message);
```

If, instead, you want to do things the hard way, you can do what you already seem to be doing which is to clear the MimeMessage.To list and add a new recipient to it and send the message again. If you do this, however, you should probably set a new MimeMessage.MessageId value:

```csharp
using (var client = new SmtpClient()) {
    await client.ConnectAsync("smtp.example.com", 587, SecureSocketOptions.Auto);
    await client.AuthenticateAsync("username", "password");

    foreach (var recipient in listOfRecipients) {
        message.To.Add(new MailboxAddress(recipient.Name, recipient.EmailAddress));
