comments.body:
Yes

To set the "body encoding", you would construct the message body like this:

```csharp
var body = new TextPart ("plain");
body.SetText (Encoding.UTF8, "This is the message body.");

message.Body = body;
```

Note that by default, for message bodies, UTF-8 is used. So if you want UTF-8, then you can even do this:

```csharp
message.Body = new TextPart ("plain") {
    Text = "This is the message body."
};
```

For headers, you'll need to bypass MimeMessage.Subject:

```csharp
message.Headers.Replace ("Subject", Encoding.UTF8, "This is my subject.");
```

You can also specify an encoding to use for each MailboxAddress:

```csharp
message.To.Add (new MailboxAddress (Encoding.UTF8, "Name", "recipient@example.com"));
```

