The problem is this:

```csharp
var inbox = smtp.GetFolder(smtp.PersonalNamespaces[0]);
```

That's not the Inbox folder, that's the root-level folder (which in most cases is a "fake" folder).

If you want the Inbox (which is a very special folder in IMAP), you can use `client.Inbox`, or you can do something like this:

```csharp
var root = smtp.GetFolder(smtp.PersonalNamespaces[0]);
var folders = root.GetSubfolders ();

// Note: the INBOX folder is case-insensitive. Every other folder is case-sensitive.
var inbox = folders.FirstOrDefault (x => x.FullName.Equals ("INBOX", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));
```

-or-

```csharp
var root = smtp.GetFolder(smtp.PersonalNamespaces[0]);
var inbox = root.GetSubfolder ("INBOX");
```

