comments.body:
Hi @namnd19 

Sorry about the delayed response.

Not all messages will have a `TextBody`, some might only have an `HtmlBody` and some might even have neither (rare, but possible).

For what it's worth, you can improve your code a bit by using Search() to get all of the UIDs instead of Fetch() like this:

```csharp
public async Task GetMails()
{
    var personal = await imapClient.GetFoldersAsync(imapClient.PersonalNamespaces[0]);
    var folder = personal.SingleOrDefault(f => f.Name.ToLower().Contains("sent"));

    await folder.OpenAsync(FolderAccess.ReadOnly);

    var uids = await folder.SearchAsync(SearchQuery.All);
    foreach (var uid in uids)
    {
        var message = await folder.GetMessageAsync(uid);
        Console.WriteLine(message.From);
        Console.WriteLine(message.TextBody);
    }
}
```

Fetch() is more expensive (especially in terms of bandwidth) than Search() if all you want are the UIDs.

Hope that helps.

