My next suggestion would be to do away with trying to treat folders individually and instead just use the `All` folder. You can filter out messages with labels that don't include the label for your particular folder, thereby drastically reducing useless IMAP query traffic.

In other words, do something more like this (if you don't want to use caching which I highly recommend you do):

```csharp
var allMail = imap.GetFolder(SpecialFolder.All);
allMail.Open(FolderAccess.ReadOnly);

var gmailMessages = allMail.Fetch(0, -1, MessageSummaryItems.UniqueId |
                                                             MessageSummaryItems.GMailMessageId |
                                                             MessageSummaryItems.GMailThreadId |
                                                             MessageSummaryItems.GMailLabels)
                                                            .OrderByDescending(o => o.UniqueId)
                                                            .Where(w => w.GMailLabels.Contains("CurrentFolderName"))
                                                            .ToList();

// apply group to get threads
var groupedList = gmailMessages.GroupBy(g => g.GMailThreadId)
    .Select(s => s.Key.Value)
    .ToList();
//apply paging to reduce ids
var finalListForMerge = groupedList.Skip(paging.skip).Take(pageSize).ToList();

var uIds = gmailMessages
    .Where(w=> finalListForMerge.Contains(w.GMailThreadId.Value))
    .Select(s => s.UniqueId).ToList();

//get messages by Uids with correct references
var messageSummary = allMail.Fetch(uIds, MessageSummaryItems.All |
     MessageSummaryItems.References |
     MessageSummaryItems.PreviewText |
     MessageSummaryItems.UniqueId |
     MessageSummaryItems.Flags |
     MessageSummaryItems.GMailLabels |
     MessageSummaryItems.GMailMessageId |
     MessageSummaryItems.GMailThreadId)
     .OrderByDescending(o => o.UniqueId)
     .ToList();
```

That removes an expensive IMAP query which should improve the time it takes to render your message list (caching would make this all faster).

Then, I would also recommend Fetching the PreviewText separately. Render the message-list *first* without the PreviewText while you have a background thread request that information and when you have it, update the message-list with that info.

