}
```

Also: With POP3, there is no such thing as a Trash folder, so deleting messages via POP3 cannot move messages there. All a client can do is delete messages.

Keep in mind that a server can *implement* deletion via POP3 as a "Move to Trash" operation, but the client has no control over this.

