No, there is not. But you can do this:

```csharp
foreach (var attachment in message.Attachments) {
    using (var stream = new MeasuringStream ()) {
        var rfc822 = attachment as MessagePart;
        var part = attachment as MimePart;

        if (rfc822 != null) {
            rfc822.Message.WriteTo (stream);
        } else {
            part.ContentObject.DecodeTo (stream);
        }

        Console.WriteLine ("attachment length = {0}", stream.Length);
    }
}
```

In the code snippet above I am using `DecodeTo` instead of `WriteTo` because I am assuming you want the decoded length, not the _encoded_ length. If that's not the case, just swap `DecodeTo` with `WriteTo`.

