comments.body:
You are writing out the MIME container of the attachment and not the decoded attachment data.

What you need to do is this:

``` csharp
var stream = new MemoryStream();
if (attachment is MessagePart) {
    var rfc822 = (MessagePart) attachment;
    rfc822.Message.WriteTo (stream);
    rfc822.Message.WriteTo (System.Web.HttpContext.Current.Server.MapPath("~/") + fileName);
} else {
    var part = (MimePart) attachment;
    part.ContentObject.DecodeTo (stream);
    part.ContentObject.DecodeTo (System.Web.HttpContext.Current.Server.MapPath("~/") + fileName);
}
return stream;
```

(Note: For the inlineattachment logic, you don't need to check for `MessagePart` because that can't happen, image parts can only ever be `MimePart`s)

