GetMessage(uniqueid) is obsolete because it requires MailKit to track UIDs which is awkward and memory expensive.

GetMessageUids() allows you to track uids yourself.

The way to use GetMessageUids is this:

``` csharp
var uids = client.GetMessageUids ();
for (int i = 0; i < client.Count; i++) {
    if (UniqueIdIsAlreadyDownloaded (uids[i]))
        continue;
    var message = client.GetMessage (i);
    message.WriteTo (path);
    AddUniqueIdToDownloadedList (uids[i]);
}
```

If you want to retrieve 100 messages in a row, you can use `client.GetMessages (startIndex, count);` or you can use `client.GetMessages (new int[] { index1, index2, index3, ... });`

Hope that helps.

